1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP07]

3
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,400
What's that sound on your end?

4
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,280
An ambulance siren.

5
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:53,079
Why is there

6
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:54,239
an ambulance?

7
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,480
I'm at the hospital.

8
00:01:58,719 --> 00:01:59,959
Mr Xu, what happened?

9
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,920
I have a stomachache.

10
00:02:02,719 --> 00:02:03,519
Nothing serious.

11
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:07,840
Get some rest.

12
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,159
Hope you feel better soon.

13
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,840
What are you two doing here?

14
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,039
You look a lot better.

15
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:25,159
Does your stomach still hurt?
No.

16
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:27,759
No? Then eat something.

17
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:28,719
There.

18
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:29,800
Okay.

19
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:30,759
I'm not hungry.

20
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:32,560
You need to eat.

21
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,520
Ambulance sirens?

22
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:39,759
Mr Xu,

23
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:41,080
why are you listening to that?

24
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:41,599
Nothing.

25
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,919
Just trying a new kind of music.

26
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,199
That's rare.

27
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,759
Never heard of

28
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:51,360
anyone switching to

29
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,759
ambulance sirens.

30
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,560
What,

31
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:56,319
life is too boring

32
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,560
so you're looking for a thrill?

33
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,000
Mr Xu,

34
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,039
Ms Ruan is here
to see you.

35
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,000
Let her in, please. Thanks.

36
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,960
How did Ruan Yu know you were hospitalized?

37
00:03:06,639 --> 00:03:07,719
Huaisong,

38
00:03:07,719 --> 00:03:09,120
you sly fox.

39
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,199
I thought you were

40
00:03:11,199 --> 00:03:12,080
chasing thrills.

41
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,479
Turns out you're chasing a girl.

42
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:15,360
Take the thermos away.

43
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,960
You can eat it yourself.

44
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,319
I'm taking it now?

45
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:20,159
Yeah.

46
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,520
How could I

47
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,919
know you skipped lunch?

48
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:44,439
You didn't tell me.

49
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,400
I didn't tell you?

50
00:03:46,599 --> 00:03:47,800
I sent you a WeChat message.

51
00:03:48,159 --> 00:03:49,159
You must've sent it to the wrong person.

52
00:03:49,159 --> 00:03:50,280
I never got anything.

53
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:07,840
[Bring me some porridge at noon.]

54
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,199
[Room 106, New District Hospital.]

55
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:24,199
[So that message wasn't meant for me.]

56
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:26,480
[Do I go in]

57
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,720
[or not?]

58
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:30,360
I want my porridge now.

59
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,240
Fine.

60
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,439
I'll go get some.

61
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:37,959
Ms Ruan?

62
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:39,240
Mr Liu,

63
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,000
are you going to buy porridge?

64
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,680
How did you know?

65
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:43,680
Please, come in.

66
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:46,920
Ms Ruan,

67
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,160
what brings you here?

68
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,120
Mr Xu,

69
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,480
your porridge.

70
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,519
That message was meant for Liu Mao.
I sent it to you by mistake.

71
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,279
I'm really sorry
-  for the trouble.
- It's okay.

72
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,319
Mr Xu,

73
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,720
I didn't know you were sick.

74
00:05:06,879 --> 00:05:07,639
Otherwise,

75
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:09,040
I never would've

76
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,319
kept you on the case so late last night.

77
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,360
It's fine.

78
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,879
[At that time,]

79
00:05:13,879 --> 00:05:15,480
[he wasn't even admitted yet.]

80
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,480
[On the way to the hospital,]

81
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:18,680
[he kept staring]

82
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,720
[at signal bars,]

83
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,399
[afraid the call would drop.]

84
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:23,160
[In case he woke others up,]

85
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,800
[he didn't turn on his mic.]

86
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:28,600
[Love does make one act like a fool.]

87
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,480
Mr Xu,

88
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,160
are you feeling better today?

89
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,560
Not really.

90
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,160
Huaisong,

91
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,360
you need to

92
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:40,319
take good care of your stomach.

93
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:41,480
Do you know

94
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,240
the stomach is sensitive to emotion?

95
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,959
When you're in a good mood,

96
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:45,720
the pain will be gone.

97
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,639
Ms Ruan,

98
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:48,800
you're a writer, right?

99
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,360
You must be great with words.

100
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,240
If you have time,

101
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,920
come keep him company.

102
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:54,680
Better mood,

103
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:56,120
faster

104
00:05:56,639 --> 00:05:57,920
recovery.

105
00:05:59,279 --> 00:06:00,199
It's an old issue.
Don't trouble her over it.

106
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,720
How is that troubling her?

107
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:03,959
Not at all.

108
00:06:04,439 --> 00:06:05,560
I'm already here,

109
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,399
and I don't have other plans today.

110
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,879
You heard that?

111
00:06:10,959 --> 00:06:12,160
She's so considerate.

112
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,040
Alright. Thanks.

113
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,720
Why are you eating it like that?

114
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,800
That's how we do it in Su City.

115
00:06:22,279 --> 00:06:23,680
All locals eat porridge this way.

116
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:26,879
How did you know

117
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,480
I'm from Su City too?

118
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:31,639
I looked into it.

119
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:38,639
It's in your WeChat profile.

120
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:45,199
Ms Ruan,

121
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:46,560
you're here to see Mr Xu too?

122
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:49,160
Mr Xu,

123
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,399
didn't you just say you weren't...

124
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,839
Alright, alright.

125
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:53,560
Drop it.

126
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:55,959
We should get going.

127
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,160
Still got work back at the office.

128
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,240
Gotta go.

129
00:06:59,639 --> 00:07:00,360
Oh right, Mr Xu,
I just saw

130
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,240
the email you
sent at 3:00 AM.

131
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,360
I'll send the files to you right away.

132
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:07,800
[3:00 AM?]

133
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,040
[Xu Huaisong said]
[he fell asleep too,]

134
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,399
[so he didn't hang up the call.]

135
00:07:13,319 --> 00:07:14,759
You mean I was sleepwalking

136
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:15,879
at 3:00 AM?

137
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:21,839
What he means is...

138
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,240
You probably dreamed it.

139
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,120
Yeah.

140
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,720
I sent it to you, remember?

141
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,319
- I sent it to him.
- Really?
I sent it.

142
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,279
Let's go.

143
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,120
See you.
Seriously?

144
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:36,680
Have a seat.

145
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:40,759
Wait, Mao,

146
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:42,199
that email was definitely from Mr Xu.

147
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,560
After all these years,

148
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,399
you still can't

149
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,439
read between the lines?

150
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:48,680
Think about it.

151
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,040
Come to think of it,

152
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:04,160
Ms Ruan does act weird

153
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,000
when Ms Ruan's around.

154
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,639
Like the day he got back.

155
00:08:06,759 --> 00:08:07,879
He made me put on that act

156
00:08:07,879 --> 00:08:09,399
about Ms Zhang being in trouble.

157
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:11,279
Then I called to ask

158
00:08:11,279 --> 00:08:12,079
when to pick him up

159
00:08:12,079 --> 00:08:13,480
but he said he hadn't eaten.

160
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,920
He really is a sly fox.

161
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,720
Mr Xu, you finished eating?

162
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,559
Yeah.

163
00:08:35,279 --> 00:08:35,679
Okay.
Thanks.

164
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,120
It's nothing.

165
00:08:38,279 --> 00:08:39,120
Get some rest.

166
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:40,440
I should head back.

167
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,519
I've sorted out and brought along

168
00:08:42,519 --> 00:08:43,039
the plagiarism
rebuttal files.

169
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,399
Take a look when you got time.

170
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:46,600
Okay.

171
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,879
Can you hand them over?

172
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:52,879
Here.
Thanks.

173
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:04,679
[She made you fried rice cakes]
[and visited you in hospital.]

174
00:09:05,679 --> 00:09:07,039
[She's clearly got a thing for you.]

175
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:09,759
[Why not make a move?]

176
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:10,919
[You might have a shot.]

177
00:09:27,159 --> 00:09:27,759
Mr Xu,

178
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,080
I'll get going then.

179
00:09:29,799 --> 00:09:30,200
Alright.

180
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,679
Okay. Have some rest.

181
00:09:33,759 --> 00:09:34,240
Wait.

182
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:37,799
There's always

183
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,399
been a chapter missing

184
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,279
from your document,

185
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,159
Chapter 23.

186
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:08,679
Huaisong?

187
00:10:24,519 --> 00:10:25,080
Yu,

188
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:27,759
would

189
00:10:28,279 --> 00:10:29,120
you like...

190
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:39,679
Can I

191
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,399
take a look?

192
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:42,519
No.

193
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:46,360
Why?

194
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,720
It's a

195
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,240
transition chapter.

196
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:50,720
It has to be important.

197
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,519
It's...

198
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,679
It's not that important.

199
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,879
I'll decide

200
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:57,600
after I read it.

201
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,559
Right now?

202
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:01,840
Right now.

203
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:03,279
Have a seat.

204
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,080
Mr Xu,

205
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,440
I didn't bring the original file.

206
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,759
It should be in the website backend, right?

207
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,000
[How does a male lawyer]

208
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,720
[know so well about the novel website]

209
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,799
[for female readers?]

210
00:11:40,759 --> 00:11:41,440
Mr Xu,

211
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:43,399
the signal in here is terrible.

212
00:11:43,639 --> 00:11:45,120
I'll send it to you when I get home.

213
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,879
The hospital has Wi-Fi.

214
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,600
Password is 66668888.

215
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:07,799
I just sent it.

216
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,360
I should get going.

217
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,279
Mr Xu, what's wrong?

218
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:23,559
Is your stomach acting up again?

219
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:24,440
I'll go get a doctor.
I'm fine, really.

220
00:12:28,279 --> 00:12:30,360
I've just been straining my eyes,

221
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,279
and they hurt.

222
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,039
[Wasn't he]

223
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,879
[admitted for stomach pain?]

224
00:12:37,159 --> 00:12:38,279
My eyes are bothering me.

225
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,440
Could you read the original for me?
Thanks.

226
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:43,600
What?

227
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,440
I still remember the plot posted

228
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,440
by The Poet online.

229
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,039
Just read your original.

230
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,440
If there are no overlaps,

231
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,960
then we can wrap this up.

232
00:12:52,279 --> 00:12:53,519
[Sure, no problems for you.]

233
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,799
[I'll be the one in big trouble.]

234
00:12:57,679 --> 00:12:58,759
No need, Mr Xu.

235
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,080
I've already checked it.
That chapter is clean.

236
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,279
The most dangerous place

237
00:13:03,799 --> 00:13:05,240
is often the safest,

238
00:13:05,639 --> 00:13:06,480
and vice versa.

239
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,840
The more convinced you are there's

240
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:10,840
no problem, the more likely there is one.

241
00:13:13,639 --> 00:13:14,440
[It's fine, it's fine.]

242
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,039
[It's the female lead's dream.]

243
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,600
[Not mine.]

244
00:13:18,039 --> 00:13:19,159
[It's just]

245
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,799
[a romantic scene.]

246
00:13:21,639 --> 00:13:23,279
[I can survive the embarrassment.]

247
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:52,000
Chapter 23.

248
00:13:52,799 --> 00:13:53,720
He Shiqian...

249
00:13:54,279 --> 00:13:54,559
He...
Never mind.

250
00:13:57,039 --> 00:13:58,399
I'll read it myself later.

251
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:00,840
Okay.

252
00:14:03,559 --> 00:14:04,360
Mr Xu, I gotta go.

253
00:14:08,879 --> 00:14:09,360
Bye.

254
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,080
[Huaisong,]

255
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:31,840
[which ward are you in?]

256
00:14:32,159 --> 00:14:33,559
[Mom and I are coming to see you.]

257
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,559
Mom, here we are.

258
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,320
Stop eating so much candy.

259
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,720
You're not a kid anymore.

260
00:14:44,159 --> 00:14:45,399
And start using floss.

261
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,240
We came for a dentist appointment.

262
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:54,399
Where are we?

263
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:57,960
Mom, you're already here.

264
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,240
Just go in and check on Huaisong.

265
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,519
He's sick.

266
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:01,279
This is exactly

267
00:15:01,279 --> 00:15:02,559
when he needs family around.

268
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:04,120
I've told you

269
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:05,399
I don't have a son.

270
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:06,919
He is not my family.

271
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,600
Oh, come on.

272
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,919
Don't be upset. Don't talk like that.

273
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,799
Go in by yourself if you want.

274
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:15,879
You lied to me.

275
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:17,559
Mom...

276
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:28,840
Huaisong.

277
00:15:32,879 --> 00:15:33,919
Let me take a look at you.

278
00:15:34,159 --> 00:15:35,799
What happened?

279
00:15:37,039 --> 00:15:37,960
Are you okay?

280
00:15:38,399 --> 00:15:40,679
You look so pale,

281
00:15:40,759 --> 00:15:42,480
like you're on your deathbed.

282
00:15:42,759 --> 00:15:43,720
If you can't say anything nice,
just shut up.

283
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:49,320
Why did you come alone?

284
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,480
Mom's really worried about you.

285
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:55,799
She's just been
swamped with work

286
00:15:57,159 --> 00:15:58,279
these past few days.

287
00:15:58,639 --> 00:16:00,600
So she asked me to come

288
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,879
check on you.

289
00:16:06,039 --> 00:16:06,720
Mr Xu,

290
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,440
I forgot something.

291
